GitWorkingDirectory_key2: Git humare working directory ke `files` mein kiye hue changes ko track karta hai.
GitWorkingDirectory_key4: abhi git koi bhi `files` track nahi kar raha hai. Hume git ko batana hoga ki usey kaun si `files` track karni hai.
GitWorkingDirectory_key5: `Terminal` khol kar apne **stories** directory mein navigate kijiye
GitWorkingDirectory_key6:
**ls** command use karke aap apne directory ke saare `files` ko dekh sakte hain.
Iss directory mein "git status" command run kijiye.
GitWorkingDirectory_key7: "git status" command use karke aap apne directory ke saare *tracked* aur *untracked `files`* ko dekh sakte hain.
GitWorkingDirectory_key8: Directory ke kisi bhi `file` ko track karne ke liye
GitWorkingDirectory_key10: "git add \*" directory ke saare `files` ko track kar sakte hain.
GitWorkingDirectory_key12: Apne Story ki `file` ko "git add" use karke git ke through track hone dijiye.
GitWorkingDirectory_key13:
"git add" ka documentation padhiye aur uska use samajhiye
https://git-scm.com/docs/git-add
GitWorkingDirectory_key14: documentation](https://git-scm.com/doc) khol kar pata lagane ki koiis kijiye.
